#. <section class="sutta" id="sn3.5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.5:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.5:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Shackles"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.5:0.3"
msgid "5. Attarakkhitasutta"
msgstr "5. Self-Protected"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.73"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.167"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.5:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, King Pasenadi said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.3"
msgid ""
"“idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko "
"udapādi:"
msgstr "“Just now, sir, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.4"
msgid "‘kesaṃ nu kho rakkhito attā, kesaṃ arakkhito attā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Who are those who protect themselves? And who are those who don’t protect "
"themselves?’"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.5"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘ye kho keci kāyena duccaritaṃ caranti, vācāya duccaritaṃ caranti, manasā "
"duccaritaṃ caranti;"
msgstr "‘Those who do bad things by way of body, speech, and mind"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.7"
msgid "tesaṃ arakkhito attā."
msgstr "don’t protect themselves."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.8"
msgid ""
"Kiñcāpi te hatthikāyo vā rakkheyya, assakāyo vā rakkheyya, rathakāyo vā "
"rakkheyya, pattikāyo vā rakkheyya;"
msgstr ""
"Even if they’re protected by a company of elephants, cavalry, chariots, or "
"infantry,"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.9"
msgid "atha kho tesaṃ arakkhito attā."
msgstr "they still don’t protect themselves."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.11"
msgid "Bāhirā hesā rakkhā, nesā rakkhā ajjhattikā;"
msgstr "Because such protection is exterior, not interior."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.12"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ arakkhito attā."
msgstr "That’s why they don’t protect themselves."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.13"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kho keci kāyena sucaritaṃ caranti, vācāya sucaritaṃ caranti, manasā "
"sucaritaṃ caranti;"
msgstr "Those who do good things by way of body, speech, and mind"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.14"
msgid "tesaṃ rakkhito attā."
msgstr "do protect themselves."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.15"
msgid ""
"Kiñcāpi te neva hatthikāyo rakkheyya, na assakāyo rakkheyya, na rathakāyo "
"rakkheyya, na pattikāyo rakkheyya;"
msgstr ""
"Even if they’re not protected by a company of elephants, cavalry, chariots, "
"or infantry,"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.16"
msgid "atha kho tesaṃ rakkhito attā."
msgstr "they still protect themselves."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.17"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.18"
msgid "Ajjhattikā hesā rakkhā, nesā rakkhā bāhirā;"
msgstr "Because such protection is interior, not exterior."

msgctxt "sn3.5:1.19"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ rakkhito attā’”ti."
msgstr "That’s why they do protect themselves.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.168"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.5:2.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, mahārāja, evametaṃ, mahārāja."
msgstr ""
"“That’s so true, great king! That’s so true!” said the Buddha. And he "
"repeated the king’s statement, adding:"

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.2"
msgid "Ye hi keci, mahārāja, kāyena duccaritaṃ caranti … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.3"
msgid "tesaṃ arakkhito attā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.5"
msgid "Bāhirā hesā, mahārāja, rakkhā, nesā rakkhā ajjhattikā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.6"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ arakkhito attā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.7"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, mahārāja, kāyena sucaritaṃ caranti, vācāya sucaritaṃ caranti, "
"manasā sucaritaṃ caranti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.8"
msgid "tesaṃ rakkhito attā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.9"
msgid ""
"Kiñcāpi te neva hatthikāyo rakkheyya, na assakāyo rakkheyya, na rathakāyo "
"rakkheyya, na pattikāyo rakkheyya;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.10"
msgid "atha kho tesaṃ rakkhito attā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.12"
msgid "Ajjhattikā hesā, mahārāja, rakkhā, nesā rakkhā bāhirā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.13"
msgid "tasmā tesaṃ rakkhito attā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.5:2.14"
msgid "Idamavoca … pe …"
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.5:3.1"
msgid "“Kāyena saṃvaro sādhu,"
msgstr "“Restraint of the body is good;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.5:3.2"
msgid "sādhu vācāya saṃvaro;"
msgstr "restraint of speech is good;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.5:3.3"
msgid "Manasā saṃvaro sādhu,"
msgstr "restraint of mind is good;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.5:3.4"
msgid "sādhu sabbattha saṃvaro;"
msgstr "restraint everywhere is good."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.5:3.5"
msgid "Sabbattha saṃvuto lajjī,"
msgstr "A sincere person, restrained everywhere,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.5:3.6"
msgid "rakkhitoti pavuccatī”ti."
msgstr "is said to be ‘protected’.”"
